Question: Do you think age restrictions on drinking are effective?
Answer:
Nope.  The most effective thing out there is knowledge.  Make underaged people aware of what this stuff does to their bodies.  Get the parents involved and have them explain that people can have a good time without putting a drink in their hands.  Spending time with kids and teaching them about alcohol is far better than just setting an age limit since people above 21 can just buy beer for people under 21